Codes in the 4xx range, usually **your request** (client) was wrong:

- 400 Bad Request – Request is malformed or invalid.
- 401 Unauthorized – You need to log in or provide credentials.
- 403 Forbidden – You’re logged in, but not allowed to do this.
- 404 Not Found – Resource doesn’t exist (classic internet error).
- 429 Too Many Requests – You are sending too many requests too fast.
